2. person held for ransom; amateur performance of Chinese opera; classifier for groups, batches, business transactions
3. (literary) fast; speedy; used in »piàolìng«; Taiwan pr. »piāo«
4. light; airy
5. white horse

pī /pi1/
1. to ascertain; to act on; to criticize; to pass on; classifier for batches, lots, military flights; tier (for the ranking of universities and colleges)
2. to drape over one's shoulders; to open; to unroll; to split open; to spread out
3. to hack; to chop; to split open; (of lightning) to strike
4. child's buttocks (esp. Cantonese); (onom.) crack, slap, clap, clatter etc
5. blank (e.g. for a coin); unburnt earthenware; semifinished product; Taiwan pr. »pēi«
6. grand
7. multitudinous; powerful
8. puppy badger
9. arsenic
10. (millet)
11. error; carelessness; spoiled silk
12. flat arrow-head; plow blade; also pr. »pí«
13. (horse)
14. Bagarius, an Asian genus of catfishes
15. wild duck

quàn /quan4/
1. to advise; to urge; to try to persuade; to exhort; to console; to soothe
2. bond (esp. document split in two, with each party holding one half); contract; deed (i.e. title deeds); ticket; voucher; certificate
quàn /quan4/
quànzhe, with the aspect particle -zhe marking a continuous state or ongoing action.

quàn /quan4/

quàn /quan4/
